<subSubSection id="6C2CC4239EB4D873214DF1281826D3E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="AC68BB636D4DBC03BE98796AB099885A" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="975D188E6B71DE4F85DD21315E5CAD5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
The size of this species in Macau ranges 18-23 mm in total length and 5-7 mm in maximum width. In the Macau SAR, this species is very scarce and has only been recorded in late spring and always in the 
<normalizedToken id="0D390D61FAD3248C27EA5E0C2EF0C21B" originalValue="Hác-Sá">Hac-Sa</normalizedToken>
area of Coloane. Like in all 
<taxonomicName id="DEEF2B912E1BB75A71C3D9609C604CA1" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1839" class="Hexapoda" family="Vesperidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Vesperidae</taxonomicName>
, the larvae are presumably subterranean, feeding on root sapwood and pupating within the soil (
<bibRefCitation id="3AB1E32CA5F7C73E611DE56A7EA17B5B" author="Svacha, P" editor="Leschen, RAB" journalOrPublisher="de Gruyter W, Berlin / Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="16 - 177" publicationUrl="https://www.zin.ru/Animalia/Coleoptera/pdf/Svacha_Lawrence_2014_handbook_of_zoology_coleoptera_vol_3.pdf" refId="B144" refString="Svacha, P, Lawrence, JF, 2014. Morphology and Systematics (Phytophaga): 2.1 Vesperidae Mulsant, 1839; 2.2 Oxypeltidae Lacordaire, 1868; 2.3 Disteniidae J. Thomson, 1861; 2.4 Cerambycidae Latreille, 1802. In: Leschen, RAB, Beutel, RG, Eds., Handbook of Zoology, 3 Arthropoda: Insecta: Coleoptera. de Gruyter W, Berlin/Boston: 16 - 177, https://www.zin.ru/Animalia/Coleoptera/pdf/Svacha_Lawrence_2014_handbook_of_zoology_coleoptera_vol_3.pdf" title="Morphology and Systematics (Phytophaga): 2.1 Vesperidae Mulsant, 1839; 2.2 Oxypeltidae Lacordaire, 1868; 2.3 Disteniidae J. Thomson, 1861; 2.4 Cerambycidae Latreille, 1802." url="https://www.zin.ru/Animalia/Coleoptera/pdf/Svacha_Lawrence_2014_handbook_of_zoology_coleoptera_vol_3.pdf" volumeTitle="Handbook of Zoology, 3 Arthropoda: Insecta: Coleoptera." year="2014">
<normalizedToken id="0A15AC04D8988602DBB2ED6842747FDC" originalValue="Švácha">Svacha</normalizedToken>
and Lawrence 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="69D34865B9B2E70C33A76A679D329A32" author="Hua, L-Z" journalOrPublisher="List of Chinese Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 612" refId="B68" refString="Hua, L-Z, 2002. List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou. List of Chinese Insects 2: 1 - 612" title="List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou." volume="2" year="2002">Hua (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, host plants for the species include 
<taxonomicName id="E263D172D4E0AC4224059AB0C1F08522" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9C314D8D183ED15604CE95971889C300" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Citrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6757CB6173A03A9FBFBABEBD9C8ED7A1" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Saccharum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saccharum sinensis" order="Graminales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis id="41DA2FF83F969EA05813CA63E8B445FC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Saccharum sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
